  "text": "Many approaches have been proposed for preventing NPEs with static analysis [21, 29ś31] . These approaches work out of the box on a subject code base, without requiring developers to initially add annotations. However, such approaches also have drawbacks. Type-based approaches like NullAway are modular and efficient, leveraging type annotations at method boundaries. In contrast, most static analysis approaches are not modular, forcing an expensive global re-analysis at each code change. The bi-abduction approach of Facebook Infer is modular [CITATION_1] but still significantly more complex and expensive than type checking. Also, null pointer issues discovered via static analysis can be difficult for a developer to understand, as they can involve inter-procedural data flow. In contrast, NullAway errors always relate to a local violation of the typing discipline, and hence can be understood by only looking at surrounding code and related method type signatures.",
